---
import SectionContainer from "../../components/ui/SectionContainer.astro";
import CTAGroup from "../../components/ui/CTAGroup.astro";
---

<section class="bg-[#04101f] py-24">
  <SectionContainer>

    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto text-center mb-16">

      <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-semibold text-white">
        Why Most Google Ads Appeals Fail — And What Google Actually Looks For
      </h2>

      <p class="mt-6 text-lg text-gray-300">
        Most advertisers submit appeals that are emotional, vague, or incomplete.
        Google reviewers are looking for structured explanations supported by policy-aligned evidence.
      </p>

    </div>

    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto space-y-10">

      <div>
        <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white">
          Google Suspensions Are Based on Risk Signals
        </h3>
        <p class="mt-3 text-gray-400">
          Google does not suspend accounts solely because a rule was intentionally broken.
          Its systems evaluate whether an advertiser presents a potential risk to users.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white">
          Google Expects Structured, Policy-Aligned Appeals
        </h3>
        <p class="mt-3 text-gray-400">
          Appeals must reference specific policies and demonstrate corrective actions
          supported by documentation.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white">
          Repeated Appeals Can Make Recovery More Difficult
        </h3>
        <p class="mt-3 text-gray-400">
          Submitting multiple appeals without resolving the underlying issue
          can lead to faster automated rejections.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white">
          Google Reviews More Than Just Ads
        </h3>
        <p class="mt-3 text-gray-400">
          Suspensions may originate from website content, verification data,
          account behaviour, or payment signals.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white">
          Not Every Suspended Account Can Be Recovered
        </h3>
        <p class="mt-3 text-gray-400">
          Some suspensions permanently restrict accounts from advertising again
          depending on the policy trigger and account history.
        </p>
      </div>

    </div>

    <div class="mt-16 flex justify-center">
      <CTAGroup />
    </div>

  </SectionContainer>
</section>